text:
Senate Republicans say they are planning some payback if Senate Democrats force procedural votes to delay the Supreme Court nomination of Amy Coney Barrett

name: politico
text: The presence of the armed security teams are a reminder of how far the nationwide protests, now entering their fifth month, have come from the mostly spontaneous demonstrations that erupted in the days after George Floyd’s killing in Minneapolis https://t.co/LOtRpJWVgX

name: politico
text:
Now, a state of tense permanence has taken hold in cities across the country where almost nightly marches proceed with clockwork regularity through shuttered downtowns.

But the routine is spiked with an air of unpredictability https://t.co/LOtRpJWVgX

name: politico
text: With weapons in the hands of people on all sides—the protesters, the police and the right-wing militias who periodically appear — any night is a cat-and-mouse test of constitutional limits in which the guardrails against deadly violence are fragile at best https://t.co/LOtRpJWVgX

name: politico
text:
And this self-proclaimed security team is trying to keep the demonstrations going without letting them go too far (via @POLITICOMag)
https://t.co/LOtRpJWVgX

name: politico
text: Speaker Pelosi is holding out one more day for an eleventh-hour agreement with Republicans on a coronavirus relief package, hoping to clinch a longshot deal as talks with Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin drag on this week https://t.co/nImAx3rlwU

name: politico
text:
Tonight's scaled-down debate between Donald Trump and Joe Biden has been transformed into more of a conversation between the candidates than a platform for them to perform to their supporters in the room
https://t.co/5IeqOYNtcJ

name: politico
text: Revelations that President Trump paid no federal income taxes for years could energize Democratic efforts to hike taxes on the wealthy should Joe Biden capture the White House in November https://t.co/WbmXxMdBv3

name: politico
text: Revelations that President Trump paid no federal income taxes for years could energize Democratic efforts to hike taxes on the wealthy, should Joe Biden capture the White House in November https://t.co/WbmXxMdBv3

name: politico
text: The health department’s $300 million-plus, taxpayer-funded vehicle to boost confidence in President Trump’s response to the pandemic is sputtering https://t.co/Pv687Ofwew

name: politico
text:
Up now on the #PresidentialDebate2020 stage: Trump and Biden on the #SupremeCourt.

Watch live: https://t.co/FwH6cSJNbA

name: politico
text:
Within the first 5 minutes, Joe Biden is talking about one of his key messages: Trump going to court to strike down the Affordable Care Act.

#Debates2020 
Live analysis: https://t.co/5JBLk7jFGY

name: politico
text:
Trump is trying to attack Biden on “socialist” health policy rather than defend his own record or his decision to argue for the Supreme Court to strike down the ACA, notes @AliceOllstein 

#Debates2020 
Live analysis: https://t.co/5JBLk7jFGY

name: politico
text:
Trump is showing early on that he'll be interrupting at will and talking right over Biden. He's going right at Biden, and it doesn't feel like Biden is comfortable with it, notes @PoliticoCharlie 

#Debates2020 
Live analysis: https://t.co/9GtPJBNm97

name: politico
text:
Trump’s argument on Covid appears to be that more lives would have been lost under Biden’s handling of Covid, without much defense of his own record on this (apart from shutting down flights from China), says @nancook.

#Debates2020
Live analysis: https://t.co/9GtPJBNm97

name: politico
text:
Trump doubles down on contradicting his own top health officials on the timing of a vaccine. He’s decrying that the vaccine has “become political,” but his own arguments about it are doing just that, says @AliceOllstein.

#Debates2020
Live analysis: https://t.co/5JBLk7jFGY https://t.co/GGXSDweAbd

name: politico
text:
Trump promised in 2015 that he would release his taxes. He never has. He’s promising to release them again. 

Biden doesn’t hammer the point home, instead he starts talking about the tax code, notes @MarcACaputo. 

#Debates2020
Live analysis: https://t.co/9GtPJBNm97

name: politico
text:
President Trump and Joe Biden have spent months sparring from afar, laying the groundwork for an intense showdown on Tuesday night.

Here are the key moments so far from their first primetime debate https://t.co/fh3oR8dGRv

name: politico
text:
Fact check: Trump said on the debate stage tonight that the U.S. is weeks away from a Covid-19 vaccine. But the CDC director has said a vaccine will likely not be widely available until 2021.

Live analysis: https://t.co/9GtPJBNm97 https://t.co/LfrltUyqQl

name: politico
text:
RT @TimAlberta: President Trump was just offered up, on a silver platter, the chance to emphatically denounce white supremacists in front of tens of millions of voters.

All he could manage to muster: "Stand back and stand by."President Trump was just offered up, on a silver platter, the chance to emphatically denounce white supremacists in… https://t.co/Wea6N0RUbw

name: politico
text:
At times, the debate was nothing more than a jumble of the two candidates and moderator Chris Wallace talking over each other.

Biden snapped at Trump just about 20 minutes in after a line of questioning on the Supreme Court went off the rails https://t.co/LqC6pBXtYm https://t.co/QqtkCxRf8v

name: politico
text:
A big takeaway from the first presidential debate: Trump once again refused to condemn white supremacists. Watch his answer when asked directly to do it: “Proud Boys, stand back and stand by.”  

Key moments: https://t.co/xHL6RIHwFL https://t.co/iK5L6WtaNy

name: politico
text: Biden argued that if Judge Amy Coney Barrett is confirmed as a #SCOTUS justice and the court overturns former Obama’s signature health care law, 100 million people who have pre-existing conditions will lose their coverage https://t.co/LrZ7u15nHe https://t.co/j0JShQQDio

name: politico
text: Trump disputed Biden's statement that 100 million people have pre-existing conditions before pivoting to attack Biden for his own health care plan which he said will “extinguish” the health care of 180 million people who currently have private coverage https://t.co/LrZ7u15nHe

name: politico
text:
According to the Department of Health and Human Services, 50-129 million Americans have a pre-existing condition.

Under Obamacare starting in 2014, insurance companies can't refuse to offer health coverage to these Americans as they previously could  https://t.co/fh3oR8dGRv

name: politico
text: And according to the Congressional Research Service, private health insurance covered an estimated 178 million Americans https://t.co/fh3oR8dGRv

name: politico
text: President Trump tangled with debate moderator Chris Wallace early in the night, repeatedly interrupting a question about why he hasn’t released a comprehensive health care plan to replace the Affordable Care Act https://t.co/n5G7JBvCac https://t.co/zlxGb1Kn6i

name: politico
text:
Biden attacked Trump for taking advantage of the U.S. tax code and vowed to eliminate tax cuts under Trump’s tax law.

Trump cut in to ask why Biden had not already done so over his past “25 years” as a senator https://t.co/Ut5FJQzDnE https://t.co/uOsmKrQGjr

name: politico
text:
Trump retorted sharply that he had “done more in 47 months than you’ve done in 47 years.”

Minutes after the exchange, Biden’s campaign doubled down, tweeting from his account that “Donald Trump is the worst president we've ever had” https://t.co/fh3oR8dGRv

name: politico
text:
“Will you shut up?” Biden said after Trump talked over him.

While talking about the future of universal healthcare, Biden asked “do you have any idea what this clown is doing? I tell you what, he is not for any help for any people needing health care” https://t.co/gFs8DDE4OI https://t.co/Acq06ZCIxC

name: politico
text:
Trump returned to a law-and-order stump speech in responding to a question about the violence that erupted in cities throughout the country this summer.

Biden accused the president of using “dog whistles and racism” in invoking the suburbs https://t.co/EGtQlxQtfj https://t.co/VWK6vyDAAg

name: politico
text:
Here's just one example of the chaotic crosstalk during tonight's debate.

Moderator Chris Wallace: “No – No, I, I – No, the answer to the question is no – No, I, sir? Sir? You know what, wait – Stop. You're going to have – Gentlemen!” https://t.co/YZOFdWMziZ https://t.co/eWvTthkAGx

name: politico
text:
Fox News anchor Chris Wallace was criticized Tuesday night for letting the first debate of the 2020 presidential cycle quickly go off the rails:

"Gentlemen! I hate to raise my voice, but — " Wallace said before getting interrupted again https://t.co/W2VMJGxFs4 https://t.co/Fh3v5wnllC

name: politico
text:
Trump came into his first debate with Biden armed with interruptions on every topic.

But no moment illustrated Trump’s determination to bend the debate to his will than when he wrenched Biden’s tribute to his late son Beau into an attack on his other son https://t.co/HA3NMVmQF0

name: politico
text:
Joe Biden explicitly called Donald Trump “racist” during an exchange about the president’s recent move to end racial sensitivity training among federal agencies.

More key moments from the first presidential debate: https://t.co/aYLRVMftZX https://t.co/LOaAeCemCw

name: politico
text:
America just learned what a pandemic-forced conversation between Donald Trump and Joe Biden sounds like.

Here's how a nearly empty room led to debate chaos: https://t.co/5IeqOYNtcJ

name: politico
text:
Incessant interjections from Donald Trump. Exasperated laughs from Joe Biden. Constant crosstalk and mockery throughout.

The first presidential debate was something to watch. Here were the most tense moments from the night https://t.co/JHz3hZzXKj https://t.co/ffWqeNsAIh

name: politico
text: In a night marked by constant interruptions and blatant fact-fudging, it was a moment that sparked a separate online melee https://t.co/T4zquSghVT

name: politico
text: Analysis: Consistency wasn’t the point. Pulling Biden, Wallace, the sponsoring Commission on Presidential Debates and everyone watching to the level of chaos where Trump has thrived in the past likely was the point https://t.co/lGyriqVXHp

name: politico
text: The first presidential debate of 2020 was a flurry of falsehoods, with Trump offering a number of evidence-free claims to defend his tenure in office while criticizing Biden's political and personal background https://t.co/IKasV1K2CV

name: politico
text: Even longtime political observers had never seen anything like Tuesday’s presidential debate. What does it mean for our democracy? 19 experts weigh in. https://t.co/M0gdslUdmA

name: politico
text:
Senate Republicans say they can get Amy Coney Barrett on the Supreme Court by Election Day, no problem. 

But to do so will require essentially a perfect confirmation process featuring almost no errors from Barrett and no slip-ups in the Senate. https://t.co/C0xbOEDqzR
